Reasoning: The paper proposes a combined model for heat demand prediction using the Elman neural network and the autoregressive integrated moving average model. This involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with the analysis of periodicity in heat demand, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the experimental results demonstrate the performance of the proposed model, which is related to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
